
** OEM Console

  - *Add* new databases

  <example>
    $ oemapp console
  </example>

** OMS

  - Oracle Management Server

  <example>
    $ oemctl start oms
    $ oemctl stop  oms sysman/oem_temp
  </example>


  - If a process hangs then use 'ps -Af | grep oms' and kill the one
    or two listed processes. See too the sysman.sh script for a
    possible solution.

** OMS Config

  - See $?/sysman/config/omsconfig.properties

** EM Repository

  OracleOemRep

** OIA

  - Oracle Intelligent Agent


  <example>
    # 8.1.7
    $ dbsnmp start
    $ dbsnmp stop
    # 9.2.0
    $ agentctl start
    $ agentctl stop
  </example>

*** OIA logs

  - ?/network/log/nmiconf.log

*** OIA services

  - ?/network/agent/services.ora

  - OIA takes the services from */etc/oratab*. So adding a new service
    to the listener.ora file is not enough. It too needs to be added
    to the /etc/oratab file.

** Install a OMS

    $ emca

** Reconfigure dbconsole and agent

  Note the emca is in the ORACLE_HOME of the database.

    $ emca -config dbcontrol db
    $ emca -config centralAgent db -repos create

** Current OMS

  - sysman/oem_temp (The default password. This must be changed after
    first time login into the *oemapp console)*.
  - sysman/delphi (oms)
  - oem_athene/delphi@nine (database)

** Deconfig dbconsole

  - emca -deconfig dbcontrol db -repos drop \
      -respFile tmp/dbconsole-response

*** tmp/dbconsole-response
SID=
PORT=
SYS_PWD=
SYSMAN_PWD=

